article.headline: McNeese State 66, Texas Arlington 63
article.story: LAKE CHARLES, La. (AP) -- J.T. Williams led McNeese State with a double-double of 18 points and 10 rebounds as the Cowboys defeated Texas-Arlington 66-63 Thursday night. Though both teams scored 36 points in the second half, McNeese State (10-8, 5-2 Southland) had a 30-27 at the half. The Cowboys also scored 23 points off turnovers compared to the Mavericks' nine. Dwight Boatner added 15 points for McNeese State. Rodrick Epps led the Mavericks (11-10, 4-4) with 13 points. Jarrett Howell and Brandon Long had 12 apiece and Steven Thomas pulled down 12 rebounds.
